                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10788WaldaMuse">Walda Muse</persName>The
                        main text is writen in a hand similar to that of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12076ZawaldaMaryam">Zawalda Māryām</persName> who wrote QSM-001
                        and QSM-007.
 Walda Muse wrote short additional texts on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 74r-v (s. Additiones 1, 2 and varia). He is the
                        scribe of MR-006 and SMM-006, but his handwriting is different from Walda
                        Muse of MR-004.<date>18th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይብል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipits of texts and of constituent
                           parts of Gadla Libānos; the names Libānos and Mäṭaʿ in texts IV-VIII;
                           names of the donors; abbreviations; the words ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡, ቡራኬ፡ and እማሬ፡
                           (ዕማሬ፡); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 
 Text in fol. 106r is written alternately in red and
                           black lines.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
