                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#74r">f. 74r</locus>
                           <desc>: Rhymed supplication for the soul of a local scribe Walda
                              Muse.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#74r">74r</locus>: እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላክነ፡ ዘአንሃልከ፨ ቅድመ፡ ጥቅማ፡
                              ለኢያሪኮ፡ በእደ፡ ኢያሱ፡ ገብርከ፨ ከማሁ፡ {ይእዜ፡} አንህል፡ ጥቅመ፡ ኃጢአትየ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ወልደ፡ ሙሴ።
                              ወኃጢአተ፡ ኲሉ፡ ሕዝብከ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#74r">74r</locus>: Lord our God, who destroyed the old
                              wall of Jericho by the hand of Your servant Joshua, now in the same
                              way destroy the wall of my sin, [the sin of] Your servant Walda Muse,
                              and the sin of all Your people.</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#74v">f. 74v</locus>
                           <desc>: A short salām-hymn to the clergymen.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#74v">74v</locus>: ሰላም፡ ለክሙ፡ ካህናት፡ አንትሙ፡ ለምግባረ፡ ሠናይ፡
                              ዘሃረየክሙ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ በሸርነቱ፡ ይምሀርክሙ፡ ለገቢረ፡ ፈቃዱ፡ ያክህልክሙ፡ አ{ፍ}ቅሩ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስትያን።
                              ትሔይሰክሙ</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#74v">74v</locus>: Peace be to you, priests! May the
                              Lord, who has chosen you for good deeds, in His goodness teach you
                              [and] enable you to perform His will. Love the Church which will be
                              good for you.</quote>
                           <note> Written by Walda Muse. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>: Pen trial: “the pen
                           which Walda Muse tried and began [writing with] on Monday, by the Lord’s
                           grace”.
 - <locus target="#74v">74v</locus>: Writing exercise
                           (beginning of the Ethiopic syllabary).
 - <locus target="#83r">83r</locus> (in the upper margin): 95r (in the bottom margin): The
                           name በርናባስ፡ crudely written in pen.
 - <locus target="#90v">90v</locus>, 91r, 98r, 105r, 106r, 109r, 111v (in the bottom margin):
                           Crude notes.
 - <locus target="#104r">104r</locus> (in the upper
                           margin): በርናባስ፡ ተስፋየ፡ ፅገ፡ crudely written in pen; (in the bottom margin):
                           ፅገ፡ ገ/ሚካኤል፡ crudely written in pen.
 - <locus target="#110v">110v</locus> (in the upper margin): pen trial. In the bottom margin:
                           note.
 - <locus target="#111r">111r</locus> (in the upper margin):
                           Note.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Fols. 76v, 83r, 87r, 89r, 92v, 95v, 98v (in the
                              upper margin): Notes indicating the beginning of monthly readings from
                              Gädlä Libānos.</desc>
                        </item>
